        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The correct behavior of the decorator is to show the class \"required\" if the field is required or \"optional\" if the field is not required, but the decorator don't do it.\r\n\r\nThe lines 318-320 of the file Zend\/Form\/Decorator\/Label.php are:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n            $decorator = new Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag();\r\n            $decorator->setOptions(array('tag' => $tag,\r\n                                         'id'  => $this->getElement()->getName() . '-label'));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nBut the correct must be:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n            $decorator = new Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag();\r\n            $decorator->setOptions(array('tag' => $tag,\r\n                                         'class'  => $class,\r\n                                         'id'  => $this->getElement()->getName() . '-label'));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAnother thing: There is no way to add one more class to the label decorator. In future versions would be possible?"
        },
